We stand on the shoulders of giants for real. Men who have done things that seem unreal nowadays.  Abel Sanchez talking about the beauty and importance of film study. For coaches and fighters if you ask me. We don’t have the likes of Emmanuel Steward, Bouie Fisher, Eddie Futch, Cus D’amato, George Benton around anymore but we have their work. We have film. We have books. We may still have a few of their students around. We should use those things to develop and build our own programs, styles. Take a little from each and incorporate them into the things that you do. Become and encyclopedia, a historian and there’s no way that it won’t help you become a better teacher. Film study is hands down one of the best things you can do to learn about the great coaches and fighters of the past. #coachmustafah #ttg #trainedtogo #boxing #atlboxing #boxinggym #boxingskills #boxingtraining #abelsanchez

Things you should know about your local boxing clubs. 

They struggle to make ends meet or find places to train. They scrape together sponsors for sending these kids to shows. A lot of the kids that do box have little or no financial means to do so and the coaches find ways to register them either out of pocket or finding sponsors. This is a volunteer organization 💯. USA Boxing doesn't pay us to become coaches.  Tthey certainly charge us for registering ourselves and the kids to box. We pay to become coaches because we love this sport and the kids in our communities and are committed to bringing different opportunities for these kids. 

This isn't your local public school sport.  Your kid doesn't get benched.  This is a sport of you and gives you what you pour into it.

REDEMPTION!!! So many layers to this weekend’s big fight but first of all congratulations to Teofimo Lopez and his team. If we listen we can hear where Teofimo Sr talks about his son going out there and boxing. Putting on a beautiful display of boxing and he did exactly that. Sr goes on to say that they aren’t going out there to kill their opponent. They were going to break him little by little which they exactly did. I went into the fight with the opinion that the outcome would come to Teofimo. If he went out there chasing a knockout and being emotional it wouldn’t have worked in his favour but if he went out there and took his time and boxed he had a very good chance of winning. Sometimes even we as coaches put a lot of stress on fighters to chase knockouts or give them wrong instructions. The whole world was on Sr’s case. Saying Teofimo should leave find a new trainer, etc but thy stayed together and corrected what I felt needed to be corrected. Congrats to them and hopefully lessons for us all. Even as coaches. Look at those feet. Two of the best fighters on the planet just went at it and Inoue looked amazing. While some may talk about the explosiveness, the power, the athleticism let’s look at his fundamentals. His base. As we can see clearly his stance is wide and his feet are flat. Planted into the ground  but ready to explode into action as soon as necessary. No energy wasted. Perpetually moving and bouncing very rarely, only in tiny increments to maintain rhythm and stay mobile. Heavy feet offer you better balance, more strength in physical exchanges, more power in your punches and make it easier to maintain composure and stamina. To each his own. There’s more than one way to skin a cat but there’s definitely a misconception that being flat footed is wrong. Plenty of fighters have fought flat footed. Not because they were flawed but because it made sense to them and it is functional. I personally like flat. Heavy foot. Study these fighters. Study the small things. Their hand placement. The way they move around in the ring. Start from round 1 until the end. Watch them more than once. You can clearly see in this video when the boxers move their heels, they of course come off the ground, and they may be pushing off the balls of their feet when they move, BUT AT NO TIME IS HE STANDING ON THE BALLS OF HIS FEET! The heels consistently touch the canvas and the heels are ALWAYS CLOSE TO THE FLOOR! The closer your feet are to the floor, the SMOOTHER, QUICKER, BALANCED and MORE EFFICIENT. I want my boxers to be just as relaxed in your boxing stance and in the boxing ring as you are walking around your living room. It’s not an an ATHLETIC CONTEST. IT IS AN ART! The more relaxed the body, the more relaxed the mind and vice versa. The more relaxed everything is, the better everything is including speed and power! #coachmustafah #ttg #trainedtogo #boxing #atlboxing #boxinggym #boxingskills #boxingdrills #sweetscience

Look at those feet. Another fight with 2 champions fighting to be undisputed. While some may talk about the explosiveness, the power, the athleticism let’s look at his fundamentals. His base. As we can see clearly his stance is wide and his feet are flat. Planted into the ground but ready to explode into action as soon as necessary. No energy wasted. Perpetually moving and bouncing very rarely, only in tiny increments to maintain rhythm and stay mobile. Heavy feet offer you better balance, more strength in physical exchanges, more power in your punches and make it easier to maintain composure and stamina. To each his own. There’s more than one way to skin a cat but there’s definitely a misconception that being flat footed is wrong. Plenty of fighters have fought flat footed. Not because they were flawed but because it made sense to them and it is functional. I personally like flat. Heavy foot.
Study these fighters. Study the small things. Their hand placement. The way they move around in the ring. Start from round 1 until the end. Watch them more than once. You can clearly see in this video when the boxers move their heels, they of course come off the ground, and they may be pushing off the balls of their feet when they move, BUT AT NO TIME IS HE STANDING ON THE BALLS OF HIS FEET! The heels consistently touch the canvas and the heels are ALWAYS CLOSE TO THE FLOOR! The closer your feet are to the floor, the SMOOTHER, QUICKER, BALANCED and MORE EFFICIENT. I want my boxers to be just as relaxed in your boxing stance and in the boxing ring as you are walking around your living room. It’s not an an ATHLETIC CONTEST.
IT IS AN ART! The more relaxed the body, the more relaxed the mind and vice versa. The more relaxed everything is, the better everything is including speed and power! #coachmustafah #ttg #trainedtogo #boxing #atlboxing #boxinggym #boxingskills #boxingdrills #sweetscience
